theorem P1_implies_closure_interior_closure_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (A : Set X) →
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) = closure A := by
  intro hP1
  -- `closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A`
  have h₁ :
      closure (interior (closure (A : Set X))) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono
      (interior_subset : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A)
  -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`
  have h₂ : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    -- First, show `A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A))`.
    have hA :
        (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      intro x hxA
      -- From `P1`, `x ∈ closure (interior A)`.
      have hx_cl_intA : x ∈ closure (interior (A : Set X)) := hP1 hxA
      -- `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)` and taking closures preserves inclusion.
      have hIncl :
          closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆
            closure (interior (closure A)) := by
        apply closure_mono
        apply interior_mono
        exact (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
      exact hIncl hx_cl_intA
    -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
    simpa [closure_closure] using closure_mono hA
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem interior_closure_interior_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior (A : Set X)))
      ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  -- First, `interior A ⊆ A`.
  have h₀ : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ A := interior_subset
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusions.
  have h₁ : closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A :=
    closure_mono h₀
  -- Finally, apply monotonicity of `interior`.
  exact interior_mono h₁

theorem P1_of_subset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hAB : (A : Set X) ⊆ B) :
    Topology.P1 B → Topology.P1 A := by
  intro hP1B
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1B ⊢
  intro x hxA
  exact hP1B (hAB hxA)

theorem P1_P2_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 (A : Set X) → Topology.P2 A → Topology.P3 A := by
  intro _ hP2
  exact Topology.P2_implies_P3 (A := A) hP2
